### Setup Script Workflow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant Setup as setup_dmg_builder.sh
    participant Project as Project Directory
    participant Shared as _shared-configs/

    Dev->>Setup: Run ./setup_dmg_builder.sh
    Setup->>Project: Create dmg-template/
    Setup->>Project: Link build-dmg.sh â†’ universal_dmg.sh
    Setup->>Shared: Check for .pylintrc
    Shared->>Project: Symlink .pylintrc
    Setup->>Shared: Check for pyrightconfig.json
    Shared->>Project: Symlink pyrightconfig.json
    Setup->>Project: Create dmg-config.json
    Setup->>Project: Update .gitignore
    Setup->>Project: Create DMG_BUILD_README.md
```

### Benefits of Shared Configs

- **Single Source of Truth**: Update linting rules once, all projects inherit changes
- **Consistency**: All projects use identical development standards
- **Easy Overrides**: Delete symlink and create local file for project-specific needs
- **Version Control**: Shared configs tracked in `.dev-tools`, not duplicated per project

